\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Zero-shot scale extrapolation. The policy is trained only on small fabrics ($\le $676 grid tiles; shaded band). With a single zero-shot rollout per benchmark it produces ADP reductions on all six held-out benchmarks. The four larger ones lie to the \emph  {right} of the training band --- out of distribution in size, up to $2{,}304$ tiles ($\sim $$3.4\times $ the area and $\sim $$5\times $ the logic of anything in the training pool) --- and every one is positive across all three seeds. The two small benchmarks (\texttt  {custom\_macbuf}, \texttt  {lightweight\_cipher}; grey) are in-size controls. Dots are three seeds (7/42/123), the tick is the median, and the line spans min--max. All reductions are against the same traditional baseline.}}{1}{figure.caption.3}\protected@file@percent }
\providecommand*\caption@xref[2]{\@setref\relax\@undefined{#1}}
\newlabel{fig:scale}{{1}{1}{Zero-shot scale extrapolation. The policy is trained only on small fabrics ($\le $676 grid tiles; shaded band). With a single zero-shot rollout per benchmark it produces ADP reductions on all six held-out benchmarks. The four larger ones lie to the \emph {right} of the training band --- out of distribution in size, up to $2{,}304$ tiles ($\sim $$3.4\times $ the area and $\sim $$5\times $ the logic of anything in the training pool) --- and every one is positive across all three seeds. The two small benchmarks (\texttt {custom\_macbuf}, \texttt {lightweight\_cipher}; grey) are in-size controls. Dots are three seeds (7/42/123), the tick is the median, and the line spans min--max. All reductions are against the same traditional baseline}{figure.caption.3}{}}
